fr.enstb.xmlcode
Class KeyValueCoder

java.lang.Object
  fr.enstb.xmlcode.KeyValueCoder

public class KeyValueCoder
extends java.lang.Object

KeyValueCoder is an utility class that allow to manipulate (set methods) properties of object (field or get/set methods pair) from values represented as String (very usefull for xml coding/decoding)

Those operations are done using the java.lang.reflect package and all developments done in KeyValueProperty class.
This class is used in the context of XML decoding using a mapping model allowing to instanciate directly object from XML strings or streams (and reverse operation).
Manipulated types are all the java primitives (int, long, short, double, float, boolean, byte, char) or a Date, a String a File or a URL)

Author:
Sylvain Guerin
See Also:
KeyValueProperty, XMLCoder, XMLDecoder, XMLMapping, KeyValueDecoder

Sets value textValue for keyValueProperty keyValueProperty for object object asserting that corresponding keyValueProperty type is a java primitive (int, long, short, double, float, boolean, byte, char) or a Date, a String a File or a URL)
